~++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++Euclide: BOOK 1 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
								The Line
JOHN CASEY: 
	II. A line is length without breadth.
	III. The intersections of lines and their extremities are points.
	IV.  A line which lies evenly between its extreme points.
THOMAS HEATH:
	2. A line is breadthless legth.
	3. The extremities of line are points.
	4. A straight line is a line which lies evenly with the points on itself.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------~
line has length.
line does not have breadth.
line does not have thickness.
a straight line is a line which lies evenly with the points on itself.
a finite straight line is a straight line which is bounded by 2 points.

